claim.claim-text:
7. A method of sample formation and imaging comprising:
a) providing an object in a vacuum chamber;
b) forming a sample from the object inside said vacuum chamber;
c) thinning at least a portion of the sample with an ion beam; and
d) imaging the thinned sample, wherein at least a portion of said sample is subjected to a electron beam, wherein said thinning and imaging are repeated at least once while said sample is inside said vacuum chamber, thereby providing a plurality of images.
